`, then wait until `t = 2`.\n\n- At time `t = `2``, take the edge `(1 → 2)` which is available from 2 to 5. You arrive at node 2 at time 3.\n\nHence, the minimum time to reach node 2 is 3.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** n = 4, edges = [[0,1,0,3],[1,3,7,8],[0,2,1,5],[2,3,4,7]]\n\n**Output:** 5\n\n**Explanation:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3604-minimum-time-to-reach-destination-in-directed-graph/3604-screenshot-2025-06-06-at-004757.png","sequence":3,"sha256":"7fa22b36d9838db10805e064fd7e1289ec3f2f87dc8135a2c1a363593c84d575","type":"image"},{"sequence":4,"text":"The optimal path is:\n\n- Wait at node 0 until time `t = 1`, then take the edge `(0 → 2)` which is available from 1 to 5. You arrive at node 2 at `t = 2`.\n\n- Wait at node 2 until time `t = 4`, then take the edge `(2 → 3)` which is available from 4 to 7. You arrive at node 3 at `t = 5`.\n\nHence, the minimum time to reach node 3 is 5.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\n**Input:** n = 3, edges = [[1,0,1,3],[1,2,3,5]]\n\n**Output:** -1\n\n**Explanation:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3604-minimum-time-to-reach-destination-in-directed-graph/3604-screenshot-2025-06-06-at-004914.png","sequence":5,"sha256":"31044030bf6d61d0c94061ddfbb880630e02df53b91a98b7d376d85e46cb0c05","type":"image"},{"sequence":6,"text":"- Since there is no outgoing edge from node 0, it is impossible to reach node 2. Hence, the output is -1.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n <= 10⁵`\n\n- `0 <= edges.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `edges[i] == [ui, vi, starti, endi]`\n\n- `0 <= ui, vi <= n - 1`\n\n- `ui != vi`\n\n- `0 <= starti <= endi <= 10⁹`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Graph Theory","Heap (Priority Queue)","Shortest Path"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given an integer `n` and a **directed** graph with `n` n