ple 2:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [3,2,3,2,3,2,3], queries = [[0,6,4],[1,5,2],[2,4,1],[3,3,1]]\n\n**Output:** [3,2,3,2]\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n| Query | Sub-array | Threshold | Frequency table | Answer |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| [0, 6, 4] | [3, 2, 3, 2, 3, 2, 3] | 4 | 3 → 4, 2 → 3 | 3 |\n| [1, 5, 2] | [2, 3, 2, 3, 2] | 2 | 2 → 3, 3 → 2 | 2 |\n| [2, 4, 1] | [3, 2, 3] | 1 | 3 → 2, 2 → 1 | 3 |\n| [3, 3, 1] | [2] | 1 | 2 → 1 | 2 |\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length == n <= 10⁴`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `1 <= queries.length <= 5 * 10⁴`\n\n- `queries[i] = [li, ri, thresholdi]`\n\n- `0 <= li <= ri < n`\n\n- `1 <= thresholdi <= ri - li + 1`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/threshold-majority-queries/","problemName":"Threshold Majority Queries","problemNumber":3636,"problemSlug":"threshold-majority-queries","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":3636,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given an integer array `nums` of length `n`.\n\nAn array is **trionic** if there exist indices `0 < p < q < n − 1` such that:\n\n- `nums[0...p]` is **strictly** increasing,\n\n- `nums[p...q]` is **strictly** decreasing,\n\n- `nums[q...n − 1]` is **strictly** increasing.\n\nReturn `true` if `nums` is trionic, otherwise return `false`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [1,3,5,4,2,6]\n\n**Output:** true\n\n**Explanation:**\n\nPick `p = 2`, `q = 4`:\n\n- `nums[0...2] = [1, 3, 5]` is strictly increasing (`1 < 3 < 5`).\n\n- `nums[2...4] = [5, 4, 2]` is strictly decreasing (`5 > 4 > 2`).\n\n- `nums[4...5] = [2, 6]` is strictly increasing (`2 < 6`).\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [2,1,3]\n\n**Output:** false\n\n**Explanation:**\n\nThere is no way to pick `p` and `q` to form the required three segments.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `3 <= n <= 100`\n\n- `-1000 <= nums[i] <= 1000`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array"